desc:
The modular wings of the ship can be modified according to requirements.

Increase the ship's armor by %s, increase armor resistance by %s, and increase the ship's HP by %s;
Reduce the ship's maximum speed by %s, decrease mobility by %s.

The modular wings of the ship can be modified according to requirements.

Increase the maximum speed of the ship by %s, enhancing the maneuverability of the ship;
Increase the high-explosive damage received by the ship's hull/armor by %s, reducing the armor by %s points.

The modular system of the ship can be changed as needed, and after the system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Ballistic weapon firing rate increased by %s, Ballistic and missile weapon ammo recovery rate increased by %s;
Ballistic weapon flux cost reduced by %s.

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to a strike wings;
Reduce the Austenite's actual engine speed by %s .

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to assault wings;
Reduce the damage of all shipborne weapons in Austenite - class by %s.

The modular system of ship can be changed as needed, and after the ship system is turned on, the ship gains the following capabilities:

Change the built-in aircraft to a support wings;
Reduce base range of all shipborne weapons in Austenite - class by %s .

The {main framework} of the ship can be changed as needed and have the following impacts:

Ship armor reduced by %s, HP reduced by %s;
Flux capacity increased by %s, flux dissipation increased by %s;
Zero-flux acceleration limit raised to %s flux.

The {main framework} of the ship can be changed as needed and have the following impacts:

Ship HP increased by %s, EMP resistance increased by %s, weapon repair rate increased by %s;
Armor and structural resistance increased by %s;
Reduce flux dissipation rate by %s.

The {main framework} of the ship can be changed as needed and have the following impacts:

Ballistic weapon damage increased by %s, the rate of fire of Ballistic weapons increased by %s;
Shield efficiency increased by %s, while the range of ballistic and missile weapons decreased by %s.

The modular tail wing of the ship can be modified as needed and has the following impacts:

Based on the current travel speed of the ship, gain %s additional flux dissipation speed;

When the ship's flux exceeds half of its max capacity, the top speed of the ship is increased %s based on the actual flux level of the ship.
